So many times I hear people talking about their curling iron curls not lasting for multiple days. 🚫

I’m here with just a quick reminder that your curls are falling out probably because you’re not supporting them with a structural product before your blowout. 🫤

Hitting them with hairspray after you’re finished is not enough! You’ve gotta support the style’s longevity from the start (when it’s damp.) 

➡️Here are my 5 favorite Oribe styling products that support your style for multiple days. 

⭐️Maximista: Volume spray + heat protectant. Literally so user friendly and easy, spray it everywhere. 

⭐️Grandiose: Hair plumping mouse that swells the style and adds lift. A little goes a long way. 

⭐️Gel Serum: A classic for gals with average or thick hair. The gel creates memory & hold while the serum nourishes and stands up to the task of a hearty weekly blowout.

⭐️Tres Set: A modern spin on mouse that adds structure and added heat protection to a style. Can be sprayed directly into the hair or into your palms for a more tradition application. User friendly.

⭐️Imperial Blowout: The ultimate blowout cream for the girl (with average to thick hair) who needs it ALL. Body, movement, nourishment, heat protection, reparative properties, the list goes on. It’s the MVP. 

📲Shoot me a Dm with your product questions, I’m happy to help. We also ship for those who don’t have an upcoming appointment! 

#ivyhouse #ivyhousesalon #oribeobsessed

☀️ Yesterday we talked products that promote memory, hold and longevity. 

Today let’s talk softening and detangling. 

If your hair needs a chill pill or an army to detangle it, I got you. 👊🏼

My latest discovery is the MR SMITH Leave-In. I’ve been using it as a step 1 detangler before wet brushing my guests. 

It’s literally a DREAM when it comes to detangling. Very softening. Use 1-3 pumps on the mid shaft and ends depending on how much hair you have. 

But YALL. Don’t forget. This would be in addition to your structural product we talked about yesterday. 

See how they serve two different purposes? Detangling and softness Vs memory and hold. You need both for great hair that lasts for days. 🤌🏼

If you’re not used to using product before you blow dry (you’re a hairspray in the end only kinda girl) then just start small, less is more with quality [concentrated] products like these. 

Grab LEAVE IN by MR SMITH next time you’re in the salon or shoot me a Dm, I’m happy to ship to you if you don’t have an appointment coming up. 🤍

Here’s to you and your good hair days 🥂

Howeverrrrr…. When your hair is curly and you put it up, it almost always wrecks your style. 

Curly refreshes have ALWAYS been hard for me. 😅

But lately they’ve been working! 😮

Here’s how I’ve been doing it. 

1️⃣ Standing at the sink, I get my hands wet. Dragging my wet hands and fingers down my hair (semi detangling it.)

2️⃣ Get a feel for what my hair needs… is it dry? Is it too soft and fluffy? If it’s too dry I would add a small amount of curl cream to my hands and also water to loosen the product. Then apply mixture to my hair as needed. I use a gel or foam (with water) if my hair is too fluffy or soft and needs added structure. 

3️⃣ I continue to apply all throughout my hair as needed. 

4️⃣ I then diffuse fully, scrunching as I go. (Remember the hair is heavily damp, NOT soaking wet)

👉🏼 Is this how you refresh? Tell me in the comments how you do it.

This part of the story is what seals the deal. 

I sure do a lot of things day in and day out. Consistent efforts, kind and respectful to those around me, doing my best to be a “good person.” 

But Im grateful to know the truth. Those things really get me nowhere. Those acts don’t save me or qualify me for eternal life. 

I am in no way worthy. No way good enough. I don’t look within myself to find happiness.

I am not enough just as I am.  Even though that’s an unpopular opinion.

My absolute favorite thing to do with hair color is to take what you’ve got [going on naturally] and enhance it.

🖤🖤🖤

Right off the top of my head….

Top 3️⃣ reasons I enjoy working for myself:

1) The schedule. Having absolute control of that is life changing.

2) The choice. I love getting to choose what colors and products I work with! 

3) The freedom. Having the freedom to market, brand and structure my business is SO FUN and freeing. 

I am absolutely not against working for someone. It can definitely work beautifully and I enjoyed that for the bulk of my career. 

I really am truly grateful for very single person who was been apart of my professional story which brought me to where I am today. 🥹

For now, and in this season. This feels right and I love that.

I hope everyone can find a situation that empowers, encourages and uplifts them as a professional so you can enjoy your weekdays. 🙏🏼🤍

This morning I was reading in a new devotional I bought titled, Upon Waking. 

It was such a good reminder. 🙌🏼

In the authors words, not my own, she wrote:

Speaking of work, we’re in a super–ambitious era. We may not be killing lions and tigers and bears, but we are killing it.

Interestingly enough, though productivity is at an all-time high, so is anxiety, which is another form of fear.

I think one part of the collective increase in anxiety in our current era is because we’ve become incredibly efficient in accomplishing a thousand tasks all the time.

We are raising babies and getting degrees and eating jackfruit pulled-pork sandwiches and listening to podcasts and exfoliating our pores all while trying to serve in church and read the Bible and resist the world, the flesh, and the devil. We are working hard and we have produced a lot to prove it.

However. When we look at our resumes and see ourselves, and all that we’ve accomplished, instead of God‘s grace, then when something doesn’t go according to plan, or work like it used to, when the strategies that have always worked for us turn around and fail us, we cope with the anxiety of it all by trying to be more productive, instead of becoming more humble. 

We strategize before praying. We work before resting. We even cut out rest altogether sometimes. All because when you know that you know that you know how to get stuff done, you start believing you are the common denominator in every victory.

You start thinking it’s not the Lord who delivered you last time and will deliver you this time but you. 😅

-I think what she’s getting at is it’s not I, but through Christ in me. To God be the glory. We shall not worship self but the Lord who made us. 

Anyways, I know that was a lot but it was so encouraging and comforting for me! I hope you are encouraged and I love you guys! 🤍🤍

This little porch in this little small town doesn’t feel quite so little really. 

3.5 years ago when my hubby and I decided to open a salon it was a lot. (For us at least) 

A lot of faith and courage. 
A lot of scariness.
A lottttt of money. 
A lot of what ifs. 
[and a lot of excitement for sure]

But in the end, it was so worth it!

For all you small business owners out there, you get it. 

I 🤍 Ivy House and the opportunity that it provides for me and for my coworkers.  It’s a space where we can be free to peruse the best versions of our professional selves.

It’s only so big and can only hold so many people but I am grateful for what it’s doing. 

Maybe one day I can help provide opportunity for more than just girls that work under this roof. That would be cool.

But for now, thank you Lord for this space and this blessing.

🤍🙏🏼🫶🏼
